post_text:
LONDONDERRY SCHOOL DISTRICT
LEGAL NOTICE OF PUBLIC HEARING
UPDATE:

The Londonderry School District will conduct a public hearing on the acceptance of the Federal CARES ESSER Grant. The Londonderry School District is scheduled to receive $168,605.83 to defray the costs associated with the COVID-19 Pandemic. Such funds shall be received under RSA 198:20-b, appropriations for Unanticipated Funds. It will take place at the Londonderry High School, 295 Mammoth Road, Londonderry, New Hampshire in the Cafeteria. The date has changed from Tuesday, August 4, 2020 to Tuesday, August 18, 2020 at 7:00pm. The public is invited to attend.

post_text:
Below please find a link to the new District News and Updates blog, located on the District web page. While this is intended to be a permanent source of information regarding the District, we are currently using this blog as a means of responding to the hundreds of questions we have received relative to our planning process for reopening schools. Due to the volume of questions received, we do not have the capacity to respond to each email individually, but many of the questions are in regards to similar information.

Initial questions and responses have been posted, and new ones will be added on an ongoing basis. We appreciate your continued patience and support as we work through these challenging times.

https://news.londonderry.org/

Another really solid week last week Londonderry. The vast majority of our students and families are keeping up their hard work. THANK YOU SO MUCH.
We are starting to see a slight increase in students not completing their work. We know the weather is getting better, but if you do not get your work done before June 10th, there will be some form for Summer School for you this summer. Don’t make that list!

post_text:
We had another great week of Remote Learning Londonderry – Nice Job. We know this is hard, and all your teachers are getting ready to wrap up the year with you by June 10th. Keep up your effort and commitment.

We want to make sure that all students try hard and do well on our “essential curriculum” this Spring. We are preparing for extended summer learning opportunities for all students, but if you are a part of the small group that is not getting their work done, more will have to be done over the summer. You have time left to get caught up. Use our remaining weeks of Remote Instruction well.

post_text: During a National Emergency, the staff of the Londonderry School District built an online school district in less than a week. We worked creatively, flexibly, and with empathy with all of our students and their families to be ready for this new experience for everyone. Our first week of Remote Instruction went very well. 95.6% of our Kindergarten through 12th grade students participated in and completed work in their classes from March 23rd to 27th. We want all our students and their families to continue to remain engaged with us and do their best in these trying times. Keep up the great work Londonderry. We will figure this all out together.

Are your children looking for a job this summer? Are they at least 14 years of age? Take a look at this!

SUMMER CUSTODIAL
We are looking for motivated people to get all our schools ready for the 2019-2020 school year. Summer custodial staff pay is $8.00 per hour. You can be as young as 14.

-Position begins around June 24th and lasts approximately 10 weeks.
-Monday-Friday, 7:00-3:30-PM.
-Apply at www.londonderry.org/employment. Choose “Click here for our latest openings”.

Applicants are chosen through a lottery process. Applicants that are not selected for a position are placed on a waiting list. You will be notified by letter as to your status.

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians,

After working closely with Microsoft for 2 weeks, they have removed the blocked that was preventing us from sending/receiving email to Microsoft-owned domains such as Outlook.com, MSN.com, Hotmail.com and others. While the messages appear to be getting delivered, they may be sent directly to your SPAM or Junk Mail folders. You may need to go into your Spam or Junk folder and mark an email as “Not Spam/Junk”. If you need help with this please reach out to your email provider for support.

With that said, we cannot guarantee Microsoft will not begin blocking us again at any time, so we continue to encourage our parents/guardians to use a non-Microsoft email to communicate with Londonderry.org email address whenever possible.

Thank you!

post_text:
Good afternoon.
This afternoon, administrators at Matthew Thornton School called for a Secure Campus at the advice of the Londonderry Police Department after a report was made of a suspicious person near the school. In keeping with our District protocol, the other three schools in the vicinity also entered Secure Campus status. The LPD investigated the response in a quick and thorough manner and determined that the report was not substantiated. The schools resumed normal operations immediately after that determination was made. At no time were students or staff in an unsafe situation, and normal operations of the schools continued throughout the Secure Campus status. While this situation proved to be unfounded, we are grateful for such a quick and decisive response by the LPD and our administrative team.
Regards,
Scott Laliberte

Londonderry Times
May 10, 2018 at 2:15 PM ·

Open for Business
The Londonderry Middle School held a grand opening last month for its our new school store, “The Storm Center,” which in the front office lobby during all lunches. Sixth and seventh grade computer students and their teachers organized the event, purchased and priced the merchandise, and designed the store logo and will be running it during lunch. Dear Parents,

We have been made aware of an issue with sending and receiving email from any Microsoft domain names such as MSN.com, Hotmail.com and Outlook.com. We are working with Microsoft to try to resolve the issue as quickly as possible but we do not have an estimated time of resolution at this point. Please use alternate email addresses to send and receive email with londonderry.org address.

Thank you for your patience!!
